After a pilot trial where we showed an substantial increase in plasma lutein levels and a increase in macular pigment optical density after only 3 months of daily consumption of a lutein-enriched egg-beverage, we now propose to study the effect these changes have on subjects with early ( undiagnosed) stages of macular degeneration.

 Age-related macula degeneration, is the leading cause of blindness in many developed countries[1-6] in older persons (usually over 55 years of age).

 Visual compromise rises exponentially after age of 70[7] with a 5-year incidence of around 1%.

